  "prompt": "What is a sulfuric acid element?",
  "response": "Sulfuric acid, often represented by the chemical formula H\u2082SO\u2084, is not an element but a compound made up of hydrogen, sulfur, and oxygen elements. It is a highly corrosive, dense, and oily liquid that is widely used in various industrial processes, including fertilizer manufacturing, chemical synthesis, petroleum refining, and wastewater treatment. Its high acidity and ability to dehydrate materials make it an important substance in both laboratory and industrial settings.",
